Rating: 4
This recipe is delicious and I'm not that fond of beets. The roasting brings out a sweeter, more subtle beet flavor, and the dressing really makes the recipe. I roast double or triple the beets, and double or triple the dressing, tossing some with the beets and storing the rest. The beets keep exceptionally well, so I just toss with fresh lettuce, pear, extra almonds, and goat cheese (amazing in this salad) as needed for up to 2 weeks. The dressing serves as a preservative I figure. I have served this on many occasions to friends and family and everybody loves it, even beet skeptics. Since discovering how well the beets keep though, I am more reluctant to share.

Rating: 4
This is an outstanding salad recipe. The almonds really make the difference. I've found that you can just toast the almonds and just put the oil with the other ingredients; it works well both ways. I've used spring onions instead of shallots as a very flavorful alternative. I plan to use the dressing for other salads too.

