Served w/ warm goat cheese, it made a nice light meal. (Whisk together egg white and water. Dip goat cheese rounds in egg, letting excess drip off, then dredge in Eng muffin or panko crumbs, pressing lightly to adhere. Chill at least 15 minutes before frying in olive oil.) Substituted pecans instead of almonds and used seasoned rice vinegar instead of red wine vinegar. I made twice as much dressing which was not as sweet as other beet recipes can be but just right for our tastes. Roasting the beets as directed was very easy.

