Rating: 4
I've never purchased beets before - much less, prepared them - but wow wee, all my trepidation flew out the window with the first bite of this salad. Cooked, cooled, sliced,then marinated the beets the night before serving; refrigerated in a single layer, in a glass casserole, covered. Flipped the beets the next morning to continue marinating. Took minutes to put together when serving. Do add some blue cheese crumbles to each serving - it compliments the flavors beautifully.

